         Good morning.          

00:08.100 --> 00:08.800
            Morning.            

00:10.900 --> 00:11.800
What's with the vegetables?     

00:11.900 --> 00:13.200
              Same as always--  

00:13.200 --> 00:14.200
            they're watching TV.

00:15.800 --> 00:17.500
  Sam, I have changed my diet.  

00:17.600 --> 00:21.100
    I'm finally eating right    
for the first time in 30 years. 

00:21.200 --> 00:23.500
            30? What were you   
             doing the other 12?

00:25.900 --> 00:27.400
    And I feel so good          
         that I thought         

00:27.500 --> 00:28.800
 we can all work on our diets.  

00:28.900 --> 00:30.400
        So I'm making up        
  this little vegetable plate.  

00:30.400 --> 00:32.400
And I figure if those guys      
 are gonna sit around and eat,  

00:32.500 --> 00:34.700
    they might as well          
     eat something healthy.     

00:34.800 --> 00:35.800
         I don't think          
    they're gonna like this.    

00:35.900 --> 00:37.000
 Oh, they'll never even notice. 

00:45.800 --> 00:47.900
         What the hell is this?!

00:48.000 --> 00:49.000
            What's wrong?       

00:49.000 --> 00:51.700
              This <i>thing</i> I found
            in the pretzel bowl.

00:51.700 --> 00:53.200
                Oh, my God,     
                 what are these?

00:53.300 --> 00:55.600
    They appear to be orange    
    and green sticks.           

00:55.700 --> 00:58.100
                          CLIFF:
        I know what they are.   
              You know, when you

00:58.200 --> 00:59.200
go in a restaurant              

00:59.300 --> 01:01.100
and you order a nice,           
big, thick, juicy steak         

01:01.200 --> 01:03.500
and they put this other         
stuff on the plate              
that you shove aside?           

01:03.500 --> 01:04.700
    Oh, you mean vegetables?    

01:04.800 --> 01:06.200
                      They can't
                  be vegetables.

01:06.200 --> 01:07.400
              There's no batter.

01:07.500 --> 01:09.600
        You guys,               

01:09.600 --> 01:10.900
you're not even                 
giving me a chance.             

01:10.900 --> 01:11.900
Now, you sit around             

01:11.900 --> 01:13.400
and you stuff your faces        
all day long,                   

01:13.500 --> 01:14.600
so why don't you stuff them     

01:14.700 --> 01:15.900
with something                  
that's good for you?            

01:15.900 --> 01:17.300
    Go ahead. Try it.           

01:23.400 --> 01:24.600
Yeah, it's not bad.             

01:24.700 --> 01:25.800
                Yeah. No, try   
                the cauliflower.

01:25.900 --> 01:27.000
        It acts like a ladle.   

